message: Before reinserting the "Emailgate scandal" section and the "Election Code Violation," someone needs to write them from a neutral POV. Those sections, as they were write, fail to comply with Wikipedia's Terms of Use.
This article contained numerous factual inaccuracies and an overwhelmingly negative tone. It needs to be professionally written and adequately sourced.

There were numerous factual inaccuracies in the article (beginning with the first sentence, which states that Martinez is Mayor Pro Tem), and it was not written from a neutral point of view. It violates Wikipedia's Terms of Use.
New Summary is sourced and accurate. Old article was poorly writing, negative in tone, and lacked citation
I restored my edits with a neutral POV, and I sent Texian Politico a Vandalism Warning
{{subst:uw-vandalism3}} - Your edits to the Mike Martinez page constitute vandalism, and I will see to it that you are blocked if you continue to make bad-faith revisions.
Texian Politico restored non-neutral POV edits. Someone, please help. He keeps screwing up the page.

/* Election Code Violation */ Not an actual violation unless legal action pursued. Wasn't in this case, apparently. Therefore, only can be called, "alleged" violation. "Minor", because not prosecutable
Controversy section needs to be pared down, and written with a neutral POV. Also lacking in basic biographical information and politician information
/* Council Emails */ Added information about resolution of NAACP complaint
/* Emailgate */ This article has a negative bias. "Emailgate" has a negative connotation. Changed the heading to make it neutral and descriptive
/* Electoral history */ City Council races are nonpartisan
Texian Politico definately knows Mr. Martinez and wants to get him. Why would you spread lies about Mr Martinez?
Non-neutral POV. Needs to be rewritten
References need to be cleaned up.
